    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 15, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🧭 Trump and Xi found progress, then Taiwan walked in\n\nThe Beijing summit ended with warm adjectives, which is diplomatic code for everyone hiding the sharp objects under the table.\n\n- **The Taiwan file:** AP says Trump left China undecided on moving forward with a record $11 billion Taiwan arms package authorized in December, plus a $14 billion sale approved by lawmakers in January.\n- **The Iran file:** Reuters reports Trump said he and Xi agreed Iran must not get nuclear weapons and that the straits should remain open.\n- **The leverage:** Trump said Xi promised not to send Iran military equipment, while sanctions on Chinese refineries buying Iranian oil remain under review.\n\n*Stability was announced. The agenda immediately filed an objection.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/trump-xi-taiwan-iran-trade-e7a3cdf161c608de152ac1c6e5755452) | [Reuters via Investing.com](https://www.investing.com/news/commodities-news/trump-says-he-and-chinas-xi-agree-iran-cannot-have-nuclear-weapons-4691149)\n\n---\n\n## 🕯️ Kyiv counted the cost of Russia's biggest barrage\n\nThe ceasefire aftertaste is gone. Kyiv is back to rubble, memorials and air-defense math.\n\n- **The toll:** AP says the death toll from a Russian cruise missile strike on a Kyiv apartment block rose to 24, including three teenagers.\n- **The scale:** Ukraine's air force called Thursday's attack Russia's biggest barrage of the full-scale invasion, after three straight days of massive drone and missile strikes.\n- **The message:** Zelenskyy visited the site as foreign diplomats and residents gathered near a makeshift memorial under the destroyed building.\n\n*The diplomacy calendar moved on. The apartment block did not.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/russia-ukraine-war-kyiv-attack-58db0cf78615952f3f090c19e104387f) | [Reuters via Internazionale](https://www.internazionale.it/ultime-notizie-reuters/2026/05/14/russia-unleashes-heaviest-wartime-drone-assault-on-ukraine-hits-kyiv)\n\n---\n\n## 🧱 Gaza's ceasefire discovered the wall called phase two\n\nThe truce is technically alive, which is doing a lot of work for one adverb.\n\n- **The deadlock:** AP says Nickolay Mladenov, the top diplomat overseeing the U.S.-brokered Gaza ceasefire, acknowledged the process is stalled over Hamas disarmament.\n- **The plan:** Trump's 20-point framework links disarmament to Israeli withdrawals, a technocratic Palestinian government, international security forces and reconstruction.\n- **The reality:** Le Monde reports Mladenov warned delays and restrictions still shape daily life, with more than 800 Palestinians killed since the October 2025 ceasefire.\n\n*Phase two remains the place where peace plans go to discover verbs are expensive.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/gaza-hamas-israel-netanyahu-mladenov-fad582f86073bd9e3345a6d309ce197e) | [Le Monde](https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2026/05/14/board-of-peace-expresses-concern-over-current-situation-in-gaza-for-survival-of-the-population_6753454_4.html)\n\n---\n\n## 🚢 Gaza's flotilla sequel left port anyway\n\nA blockade, a previous interception and a pile of diplomatic warnings somehow did not make this voyage less likely. Strange how symbolism works.\n\n- **The departure:** AP says more than 50 Global Sumud Flotilla vessels left Marmaris, Turkey, on Thursday carrying activists and humanitarian aid toward Gaza.\n- **The context:** Israel intercepted a previous convoy near Crete on April 30, initially holding about 175 activists.\n- **The argument:** activists frame the trip as an aid mission and challenge to the naval blockade; Israeli officials say early interdiction was necessary because of the number of boats.\n\n*The sea lane is now also a courtroom, press conference and pressure tactic.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/turkey-gaza-aid-flotilla-23e533a49935fd911c4bdabdd06446e5) | [Reuters via StreetInsider](https://www.streetinsider.com/Reuters/Gaza%2Baid%2Bflotilla%2Bsets%2Bsail%2Bagain%2Bafter%2BIsraeli%2Binterceptions/26492233.html)"
  }
